cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC

This paper deals with the creation and annotation of a large corpus of historical Spanish texts, which is relevant to the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), digital libraries (cs.DL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also describes the application of statistical machine translation techniques to modernize the spelling of the historical texts, which is relevant to the subfields of natural language processing (NLP) and machine translation (MT) within cs.CL.
